   135|/**
   136| * Supabase session storage adapter.
   137| *
   138| * IMPORTANT: We use AsyncStorage (not SecureStore) because Supabase session
   139| * payloads (access_token + refresh_token + user JSON) routinely exceed 2KB,
   140| * which is above expo-secure-store's per-value limit on Android. When the
   141| * limit is hit, setItemAsync fails silently and the session is never persisted
   142| * — causing the user to be logged out every time the app is closed.
   143| *
   144| * AsyncStorage is the storage layer recommended by the official Supabase
   145| * Expo/React Native guide and supports payloads of any practical size.
   146| *
   147| * On web, AsyncStorage transparently uses localStorage. SecureStore is no-op
   148| * on web, so this adapter also fixes web persistence in Expo web builds.
